{"word":"H5230 - נָכַל - nâkal - naw-kal' - Beguile","slug":"H5230","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָכַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâkal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-kal'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beguile"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05DB;&#x05DC; - na&#x0302;kal</b> - <i>naw-kal'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>defraud</i>, that is, <i>act treacherously: - </i>beguile, conspire, deceiver, deal subtilly."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3596\">H3596</a>, <a href=\"#/H5231\">H5231</a>, <a href=\"#/H5233\">H5233</a>"}]}